headline: Delta isn't 'perpetual motion machine' despite 2026 growth promises
summary: Delta Air Lines (DAL) stock is stumbling in Tuesday's pre-market trading after the airline operator reported fourth quarter earnings that beat estimates, while revenue fell just shy of expectations. Additionally, Delta's full-year earnings forecast for 2026 proved to be more conservative than what Wall Street had projected. Morningstar equity analyst in aerospace and defense Nicolas Owens examines Delta's promises of growth, to which he says that the current travel market "isn't a perpetual motion machine." To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Morning Brief.

headline: Markets Fall From Record Highs Ahead of Earnings and Inflation Data
summary: Stocks looked set to fall on Tuesday, with investors reluctant to make any major moves ahead of the start of fourth-quarter earnings season and a consumer price index inflation print.  The Dow and S&P 500 both extended their record-breaking runs on Monday, hitting new closing highs as investors managed to shake off the worst of their worries about the independence of the Federal Reserve. raw.summary: Stocks looked set to fall on Tuesday, with investors reluctant to make any major moves ahead of the start of fourth-quarter earnings season and a consumer price index inflation print.  The Dow and S&P 500 both extended their record-breaking runs on Monday, hitting new closing highs as investors managed to shake off the worst of their worries about the independence of the Federal Reserve.  The dip in futures probably reflects some apprehension ahead of the December CPI report, which will help decide if the Fed has scope to cut interest rates.
